type="local"
addr="ayberkt">Ayberk Tosun</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>axt-004B</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
    Denote by <fr:tex>(B,  \beta )</fr:tex> the small basis of <fr:tex>L</fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex>(I,  \iota )</fr:tex> be a
    <fr:tex>\mathcal {U}</fr:tex>-small family. We need to show that it has a greatest lower bound.
    Consider the family of lowerbounds for <fr:tex>(I,  \iota )</fr:tex>:
    <fr:tex
display="block">        \mathfrak {L}_ \iota           \vcentcolon \equiv             \left (              \left ( \sum _{ b \  : \  B }  \prod _{ i  :  I }  \beta (b)  \le   \iota (i) \right ),  \beta   \circ   \mathsf {pr}_1             \right ),     </fr:tex>
    which is a small family. We claim that the join
    <fr:tex>\bigvee   \mathfrak {L}_ \iota</fr:tex> is the greatest lower bound of <fr:tex>(I,  \iota )</fr:tex>.
    <fr:ul><fr:li>
        First, notice that it is obviously a lower bound because for any
        <fr:tex>i : I</fr:tex>, <fr:tex>\left ( \bigvee   \mathfrak {L}_ \iota \right )  \le   \iota (i)</fr:tex>
        since <fr:tex>\iota (i)</fr:tex> is an upper bound of <fr:tex>\mathfrak {L}_ \iota</fr:tex> by
        construction.
      </fr:li>
      <fr:li>
        Let <fr:tex>l</fr:tex> be a lower bound of <fr:tex>(I,  \iota )</fr:tex>. By the assumption that <fr:tex>(B,          \beta )</fr:tex> is a basis for <fr:tex>L</fr:tex>, we know that there exists a family <fr:tex>(J_l,          \gamma _l)</fr:tex> such that <fr:tex>l =  \bigvee _{j : J_l}  \beta ( \gamma _l(j))</fr:tex>.
        Therefore, it suffices to show
        <fr:tex
display="block">            \bigvee _{j : J_l}  \beta ( \gamma _l(j))              \le             \bigvee   \mathfrak {L}_ \iota .         </fr:tex>
        For any <fr:tex>j : J_l</fr:tex>, the element <fr:tex>\beta ( \gamma _l(j))</fr:tex> clearly falls in
        <fr:tex>\mathfrak {L}_j</fr:tex> itself since <fr:tex>\beta ( \gamma _l(j))  \le  l</fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
